                              set(s) that currently claim them, WITHOUT
                              ejecting. Same underlying logic as
                              'eject --release' and 'create --force':
                              if other members survive, the set stays
                              alive (Degraded); if all members are
                              released, the set is deleted. Confirms
                              before any destructive action.
  ${C_CYAN}smart${C_RESET} [<disk>]                Detailed SMART drill-down for one disk:
                              overall health, pre-failure attributes (with
                              non-zero "killer" highlight), self-test log,
                              and the firmware error log. The error log
                              and self-test log answer 'was this drive
                              ever in trouble in the past' - the daemon's
                              'health' command never reads those.
                              Auto-detects '-d <type>' for USB/TB
                              enclosures. Same as 'health --disk <N>'.
